Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 5/1/00
(I have taken three days for vacation)


ClearCase Migration

The migration of the DSP code to ClearCase has completed.  Now the dpi,
bitshaper and statmux directories all reside in the same parent directory.
And both the DSP and PPC code are all under the same VOB.  This set up
will release the burden of having to resynchronize both parts of the code
regularly.  Also an integration branch for DPI is also created for the DPI
development.


DPI Development

The first priority right now is the NCTA demo.  We will demonstrate single
ad on top of DiviCom bitstream.  Reliability seems to be pretty good now
for this setup.  But occasionally we see picture breakups, which are caused
by too much delay in the box so that all TP buffers are used up in the dpi
side for the accumulated data.  I am trying to adjust the delay related
parameters in dpi and statmux to avoid this problem.

We have also made some progress in the merging the statmux executables for
bitshaper and dpi.  Jinbo has help me add an environment parameter which
PPC will pass to all DSP at startup.  With this new feature users can
configurate the DSP codes with the bootloader.  I am modifying the DSP
code to accept this parameters.  After this is done, we can configure
the statmux to support either bitshaper or dpi modes by setting the correct
delay parameters.

